{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01F1aUr2SZLJihkByZhRJcyG","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→---\n     2→name: structured-logging-contract\n     3→description: Insert consistent method/step structured logging lines into target functions using jig.\n     4→---\n     5→\n     6→# Structured Logging Contract (Jig)\n     7→\n     8→Use this skill to enforce stable observability signals.\n     9→\n    10→## Required Variables\n    11→\n    12→- `target_file`\n    13→- `function_name`\n    14→- `event_namespace`\n    15→- `step_name`\n    16→- `entity_id_expr`\n    17→\n    18→## Usage\n    19→\n    20→```bash\n    21→jig run ${CLAUDE_SKILL_DIR:-.claude/skills/structured-logging-contract}/recipe.yaml --vars '{\n    22→  \"target_file\": \"services/core_service.py\",\n    23→  \"function_name\": \"create_record\",\n    24→  \"event_namespace\": \"core_service.create_record\",\n    25→  \"step_name\": \"validate_input\",\n    26→  \"entity_id_expr\": \"record_id if \\\"record_id\\\" in locals() else None\"\n    27→}'\n    28→```\n    29→\n    30→Notes:\n    31→- This eval skill currently targets `def create_record` in `services/core_service.py`.\n    32→- The `.done` event is inserted immediately before the `return {` line in that function.\n    33→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it looks malicious. If it does, you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer high-level questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c24501af-f774-4ae2-a492-890f1cc9eef8","uuid":"b62d8529-c716-4f73-b591-0a4cc3427a96"}
